summary: Lyrics:  The desert is cruel under unjust rule Fear and hate may burn These we must unlearn It’s time to go sun’s getting real...
caption:
Lyrics:

The desert is cruel
under unjust rule
Fear and hate may burn
These we must unlearn

It’s time to go
sun’s getting real low

Gentle moon will rise
Child shut your eyes
Together we’ll be
Child don’t you see?

It’s time to go
sun’s getting real low 

Do not rage and weep
only love will keep
let pain fade away
and only love stay

It’s time to go
sun’s getting real low 

Let sleep soothe and heal
Tomorrow we’ll steal
from this painful place
towards a land of grace

It’s time to go
sun’s getting real low

Notes:
Inspired by the the lullaby in Avengers (2012) used to calm the Hulk down and transform back into Bruce Banner and comics Bruce Banner’s backstory. I imagined it’s something Rebecca Banner would sing to her son.

The desert is a reference to both of Bruce’s origins.

Brian Banner, Bruce’s father, in the comics was employed as a scientist at Los Alamos, New Mexico by the US government. It’s after those experiments and he was fired that Brian was even more convinced he shouldn’t have children.

And New Mexico is also where Bruce saved Rick Jones from the gamma explosion which turned him into the Hulk.

title: Running From My Shadow
body:
Loki has escaped the Asgard prison, again.

Soft Praise To a Hard Lie

It had become one of his favorite hobbies, if not the only one. Sneaking out of prison every other day was something that filled Loki with joy, whether it was to steal something or play pranks on Thor…
